\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529587\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529587\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lip1665702911482.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lip1665702911482.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lip1665702911482.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lip1665702911482\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Locking Behavior With an Entity Service\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When a component entity access the database via and entity service, the data is locked by the entity service. The entity service has the same locking behavior as a normal database entity, except when cautious locking is used. In this case the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ulock</span> operation in the entity service is activated by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lock</span> statement of a component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"lip1665702911482__context_w4330ab1b5b1_w4331ab1b5_w4332ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lip1665702911482__p_d44024e1_d44025e1_d44026e1\">For entity services, optimistic locking works in the same way as for other components. Paranoid locking is run using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read/lock</span> command in the entity service.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lip1665702911482__p_d44027e1_d44028e1_d44029e1\">For cautious locking, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ulock</span> operation in the entity service is activated by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lock</span> statement of a component. All fields of the occurrence are locked because the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ulock</span> operation usually contains the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lock</span> statement.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"lip1665702911482__fig_d44030e1_d44031e1_d44032e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Locking Through an Entity Service</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Locking via entity service\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/lockinginentityservice.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lip1665702911482__p_d44036e1_d44037e1_d44038e1\">When a lock is requested:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"lip1665702911482__li_d21848e1_d21849e1_d21850e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The lock trigger in the component is activated.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"lip1665702911482__li_d21851e1_d21852e1_d21853e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The lock trigger contains a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lock</span> statement, which activates the entity service's <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ulock</span> operation.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"lip1665702911482__li_d21854e1_d21855e1_d21856e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The entity service locks causes the DBMS connector to lock the row in the database.\n            </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oys1665702561153.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Optimistic Locking</a><p>Optimistic locking postpones locking the occurrence until the modified data is actually stored. This causes the lock to be applied at the last possible moment, which can result in considerable performance improvements in multiuser environments, especially for On-line Transaction Processing (OLTP).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmk1665702703785.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Cautious Locking</a><p>Cautious locking causes an occurrence to be locked at the time that a user makes the first modification to a database field in the entity, or when an erase statement is issued in a valid context. (For erase to be valid, the data must come from the database.) Cautious locking is the default Uniface locking method.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tiv1665702707129.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Paranoid Locking</a><p>Paranoid locking causes the occurrence to be locked as soon as it is read. This is achieved with the read/lock statement.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529587\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529587\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Locking Behavior With an Entity Service Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Locking Behavior With an Entity Service When a component entity access the database via and entity service, the data is locked by the entity service. The entity service has the same locking behavior as a normal database entity, except when cautious locking is used. In this case the ulock operation in the entity service is activated by the lock statement of a component. For entity services, optimistic locking works in the same way as for other components. Paranoid locking is run using the read/lock command in the entity service. For cautious locking, the ulock operation in the entity service is activated by the lock statement of a component. All fields of the occurrence are locked because the ulock operation usually contains the lock statement. Figure 1. Locking Through an Entity Service When a lock is requested: The lock trigger in the component is activated. The lock trigger contains a lock statement, which activates the entity service's ulock operation. The entity service locks causes the DBMS connector to lock the row in the database. Related Links Optimistic Locking Optimistic locking postpones locking the occurrence until the modified data is actually stored. This causes the lock to be applied at the last possible moment, which can result in considerable performance improvements in multiuser environments, especially for On-line Transaction Processing (OLTP). Cautious Locking Cautious locking causes an occurrence to be locked at the time that a user makes the first modification to a database field in the entity, or when an erase statement is issued in a valid context. (For erase to be valid, the data must come from the database.) Cautious locking is the default Uniface locking method. Paranoid Locking Paranoid locking causes the occurrence to be locked as soon as it is read. This is achieved with the read/lock statement. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}